GitHub Tutorial
--------------------
git config user.name "name"
git config user.email "email"

For global
-----------
git config --global user.name "name"
git config --global user.email "email"
-----------
git remote set-url origin <Generated Token>@github.com/Alwinkunjachan/Reponame.git (General local command for a repo)

Essential Commands: 
----------------------
git init
git status
git add "fileName"
git add .
git restore "FileName"
git restore .
git commit -m "message"
git push -u origin "BranchName" (-u flag should be used only once which is the intial push)
git log
git checkout "commit-id"
git checkout "BranchName"
git checkout -b "BranchName"
git branch
git merge "BranchName"
git reset --hard HEAD~2

Stashing the changes
----------------------
# You're in the middle of something
git status

# You decide to stash it
git stash push -m "Work in progress: footer fixes"

# Do something else
git checkout another-branch

# Come back to your work
git checkout main
git stash list
git stash apply stash@{0} To apply the specific stash from the list without removing it from the stash list
git stash pop : To apply stash to the current repo and remove it from the stash list
git stash apply : To apply the most recent stash from the list and this wont remove the stash from the list
To clear the stash : git stash clear

